description:
Continuing their new exploration of literary icons, Dynamite Entertainment presents the ultimate mystery as they unveil Sherlock Holmes! Written by Leah Moore and John Reppion with reverence and a modern edge, artist Aaron Campbell completes the Victorian mood under the striking and iconic John Cassady covers.
Issue #2 finds Holmes in jail, fighting for his very life as "The Trial of Sherlock Holmes" continues!
name: The Trial Of Sherlock Holmes, Part Two: A Locked Room

description:
Meet Cat Curio, intrepid investigator and babysitter as she investigates the strange case of The Mad Mad Mailman, and stumbles upon the trail of the ominous BLACK LAMP SOCIETY! And, in the present, Cassie, Vlad and Lisa chase a pet-pureeing snow blower through the horrors of rural Michigan in BLOOD BLOWER!

It's a HACK/SLASH DOUBLE FEATURE! TWO tales of blood and terror, one set in the past and one in the present!
name: Double Feature: Mad, Mad Mailman & Blood Blower

description: Shadows are born from Light...Born of noble blood, Deshwitat Rudbich became an outcast after being infected by the Vampire curse. Now he's reduced to drinking the blood of his former countrymen in order to survive...but the Light can always banish Shadow. Three hundred years ago, Deshwitat was banished to a prison of stone by the Sorcerer of Light, Kalutika. And there he would have remained for eternity, had fate not intervened. Resurrected to the present day, he now seeks revenge. Light and Darkness are not necessarily aligned with good and evil. Kalutika, once an agent of goodness, now uses Light Magic in his plot for domination. Deshwitat is the only one who can possibly stand against him, but as proven 300 years ago, his Dark Magic is unable to defeat Kalutika. In order to defeat his nemesis, Deshwitat must do the unthinkable--a vampire and master of Dark Magic must learn to harness the power of Light Magic. Impossible? Western sorcerers have always assumed so, but a group of Buddhist monks in China claim that they have done just that. So, accompanied by his reluctant companions, Deshwitat travels east to change destiny.
name: Vol. 2

description: An experiment in synthesis...A puppet of flesh made by Buddhist monks, Beryun is a living Yin Yang symbol, a perfect synthesis of Light and Dark magic. She is a creature of opposites. Beautiful, yet deadly--spiritual, yet soulless. The Dark magician and vampire Deshwitat came to China to visit her creators in the hope that they could teach him Light Magic. A wandering swordsman who cannot die... Three hundred years ago, Rett Buttler was one of Deshwitat's only friends. After the Light Sorcerer Kalutika imprisoned Deshwitat, Rett fought to avenge his friend and would have died, had his opponent not had other plans. Kalutika cursed Rett with immortality so that he would live to see the Armageddon that the Light Sorceror would bring forth. An unexpected savior...Deshwitat began his journey seeking only revenge, but now he has the weight of the world on his hands. His enemy, Kalutika, is prophesized to bring about the end of the world, and Deshwitat must master Light Magic in order to stop him. When Eastern monks fail Deshwitat, only one option remains to him - he must travel west to the very source of Light Magic...The Vatican.
name: Vol. 3

description: Deshwitat's journey to The Vatican has some unexpected consequences. He is set upon by a group of Priests and is on the verge of death, when visions of Lilith and Kalutika inspire him to a miraculous escape...
name: Vol. 4

description: Deshwitat, Rett, Millenear, Remi, and Beryun face unbelievable hazards in the bowels of The Vatican...and, as a result they truly begin to bond as a team. Deshwitat realizes in the course of their travails that he does not need to master Light Magic--he only needs to refine and strengthen his Dark Magic.
name: Vol. 5

description: While reading a volume she found in one of the Vatican's secret archives, Millenear begins to unravel the tragic events of 1624, in which the true nature of Deshwitat's and Kalutika's entangled lives is revealed...
name: Vol. 6

description: Out of the Frying Pan... Before Rett and Kal can fully deal with Kalutika's otherworldly origins, Father Daniel brings some troubling news. Into the fire... The corrupt Cardinal Josimov charges Deshwitat's beloved Lilith and Kualutika's sister Danube of being witches...an accusation that is punishable by death! Flames of hatred... As the 'Day of Promise' draws closer, the first step in the prophecies begin to come to pass.
name: Vol. 11

description: The Fantastic Four meets up to stop the rebirth of Kalutika--his rebirth would mean destruction of the Earth and all of its inhabitants. Yosimuf sends his army of soldiers and monsters to stop the group. Will the team make it in time? Or is this the end of the world as we know it?
name: Vol. 12

description: The battle between Millenear and Marlowe Midius begins. Despite the fact that Millenear can easily beat Midius, she uses the power of light, a dangerous magic, since she is no longer human but a vampire whose body is damned. Meanwhile, Grey tears through the competition as his next opponent is no match for him. Afterward, Desh faces of against Poison Ash. However, her attacks don't faze him at all, forcing her to use her last resort...
name: Vol. 16

description: A Fallen Comrade... As an injured Deshwitat recovers from wounds received in the Vampire Lord Tournament arena, he wrestles with his conscience over killing Millenear. The fact that she expressed her love for him seconds before dying, makes the death of the girl all the more tragic. A Terrifying Trial... Desperately struggling to stay alive within the depths of the Vatican's "Tower of Trials" Remi and Eiji muster all of their courage as they battle endless subterranean monstrosities. But when they finally contact the exorcism team, The Order of St. Michael, will the priests deign to help a vampire? A Final Battle... And now the moment is at hand. Deshwitat has sacrificed his own blood and the blood of his friends to get to this point--the final championship round of the Vampire Lord Tournament! It is a true death match, but if Deshwitat dies it could also mean the extinction of the entire Vampire Race!!
name: Vol. 19

description: With the end of the world fast approaching, preparations continue for the final confrontation with Kalutika, the insane "God of Light." Deshwitat carries on with his training in the “Monarch’s Room,” while the rest of the team arrives in Hong Kong and resumes their desperate attempt to bring Millenear back from the Sand of Death. As unexpected allies turn up to aid in the fight against Kalutika, the team readies itself for a fight to the finish, with the fate of humanity at stake!
name: Vol. 22

description: Now serving as a Major in the Sacred Knights Brigade, Kalutika Maybus gains a fearsome ally in Rett Butler, a Robin Hood-esque bandit imprisoned and awaiting execution. Meanwhile, Kal's activities are under close scrutiny by the machiavellian Father Josimov, who is obsessed with an undisclosed destiny that he is certain Kal with fulfill. It isn't long before Kal and friends are overrun by a horde of ravenous vampires, and eventually confronted by the creature responsible for their unholy existence--the vampire Deshwitat.
name: Vol. 7

description: Major Kalutika has made quite a name for himself in the Sacred Knights. But while on a routine escort involving Lilith Servino, the comely daughter of a wealthy church elder, Kal's squad is ambushed by a local tribe of bandits bent on kidnapping her. With Rett back at the outpost it seems as if all hope is lost...until an unwilling hero makes an entry.
name: Vol. 8

description: When Kalutika's company attempts to rescue Lilith, they confront quite a quagmire in the Swamp Clan, a monstrous group of bandits who want nothing more than to rush in for the kill. The battle heats up until the sun sets--and the vampire Deshiwatat rises, emerging to weary warriors on the battlefield. Is he a ray of hope or simply a prelude to greater darkness?
name: Vol. 9

description: The golden years of the vampire Deshwitat unfold, as he believes he has finally found his place in this world alongside his friends Kalutika and Rett. However, not all that glitters is gold as an enigmatic robed man brings news of an ominous 'Day of Promise' that is somehow entwined with Kal's birthday and may alter the course of Deshwitat's and Lilith's future...forever!
name: Vol. 10

description: The Vampire Lord Tournament begins! Still reeling from the reappearance of their missing comrade--Millenear--Deshwitat and the team are instructed in the rules of this deadly contest. The field of contestants is as vast as it is formidable, but none of the potential opponents unnerves Deshwitat more than Millenear! Even though she has sworn to kill him, Millenear begs Deshwitat not to fall in battle before they can face each other in the ring. This may be a difficult promise to keep when Deshwitat goes toe to toe with the vicious vampire Santana!
name: Vol. 15

description: Rett and the crew make a final, desperate attempt to aid Deswhitat in defeating the unpredictable Mr. Grey. But with their one-time mentor Draistail turning traitor, how can they possibly hope to succeed? The action-packed Vampire Lord Tournament reaches its zenith!
name: Vol. 20

description:
A Stunning Revelation... Just as he is about to destroy Mr. Grey in the final round of the Vampire Lord Tournament, Deshwitat is confronted with a terrible truth regarding his lost love, Lilith! A Pyrrhic Victory... Deshwitat L. Rudbich is now the Lord of the Vampires. But at what cost? And once he learns of the price to be paid in order to defeat Kalutika, will he decide all has been for naught?! A Reunion Delayed... Rett, Remi and the team desperately want to revive their fallen comrade, Millenear. But before this can be done, they must first defeat a foe from their past, now deadlier than ever!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 83: The Vampire Lord
  • Chapter 84: A History of Vampires
  • Chapter 85: The Monarch's Room
  • Chapter 86: Exceeding the Limit
name: Vol. 21

description: Desh in his illusion created by Poison Ash's spell almost loses the fight but he comes back strong as he decides to give Kalutika one last blow before he dies. So, thinking that Ash is Kal, he gives Ash one blow and the spell is broken. Realizing that Ash created this illusion, he beats her. Millenear makes a slip in her conversation with Grey and ends up revealing the past of his parents.
name: Vol. 17

description: Rebirth returns to the present! After adding a new comrade to their ranks, Deshwitat and the team travel to New York City to enlist the help of a secret ninja society. But when they discover that the clan's ranks have been decimated by a group of modern day vampires, Deshwitat realizes that he may have simultaneously reconnected with his own kind and found a deadly new enemy in the shadowy guise of "Mr. Grey"--Lord of the Vampires.
name: Vol. 13

description:
Centaur Publications published Amazing-Man Comics, created by Bill Everett and Lloyd Jacquet, in September 1939.  This comic featured the adventures of John Aman alias Amazing Man.

Amazing-Man Comics ran from issue #5 to #26, ending the series in February 1942.
Amazing-Man Comics #5 was the first issue of this comic.  The reason Centaur started at issue 5 was to create the illusion that the character had been around for a few months.  People had become reluctant to buy a first issue back in the golden age of comics because there was a good chance the character in the first issue would never be seen again.
name: Amazing-Man Comics

description: When the would-be Vampire Lord Grey captures Millenear, Deshwitat and the gang race to her rescue. However after exhausting themselves against the seemingly inexhaustible Grey, the heir-apparent to the Vampire throne challenges Deshwitat to another battle...one which will take place at the tournament to decide the new Lord of the Vampires! One thing is painfully clear--Deshwitat will have to learn to fight less like a human and more like a vampire if he plans to defeat Grey at the tournament!
name: Vol. 14

description: AMERICAN SON continues. Spider-Man goes up against Venom and Bullseye as he prepares to infiltrate the Dark Avengers headquarters. Meanwhile Harry’s life takes a dramatic turn now that he’s reunited with Lily and wedding plans continue for two lucky Parker pals.
name: American Son Part 3

description: Inaba and Remi enter the Tower of Trials for the ultimate test. Finally, Millenear faces off against Deshwitat and displays incredible power. Rett learns from Grey that whether Millenear lives or dies, something special about her identity will soon be revealed.
name: Vol. 18

description: Having turned his back on his life as a super hero, the legendary Savior 28 sets out to transform himself... and the world. But a humiliating public debacle shows 28 that change isn't as easy as he imagined... and so he sets off on a global journey of self-discovery that sows the seeds of his own tragic downfall.
name: The Whole World Is Watching

volume.name: The Life and Times of Savior 28

description: New recruits Rock & Roll and Breaker infiltrate Chimera's stronghold with the rest of the G.I. Joe team! Things are going from bad to worse and it all leads up to our big finale next issue!

Traveling the Louisiana back roads with something awful stored in his trunk, Frank Castle stops at a service station on the edge of the bayou…and steps into a world of unspeakable horror. Patrolling the depths of hell, the Punisher has crossed paths with some unsavory characters, but noting has prepared him for the unspeakable depravity of the Geautreauxs. Explicit Content
name: Welcome To The Bayou

description: It's a war that has raged for decades but who are the combatants, and what is their unexpected connection to the Earth of centuries past? The crew of the U.S.S. Hood will have only hours to find out, or die trying!
name: Shadows of the Past

description: On the road again in their pursuers' post-apocalyptic RV, the kids race to save a mortally wounded teammate! But a stopover in a small town governed by Super-Villains might spell doom for the entire team! It's Gen13 versus the 'lost generation' from NUMBER OF THE BEAST as the kids get schooled in what it means to be super.
name: Teenage Wasteland, Part 10 - A Town Called Malice

description: Grandpa Max has a secret past, and it's about to ruin his ski vacation! Can Ben save the day? Plus, the Kids Next Door!
name: Blast From The Past; Operation: T.O.O.T.H.F.A.I.R.Y.; S.H.A.K.E.; R.A.T.T.L.E.; R.O.L.L.

first_appearance_teams.name: Delightful Children From Down The Lane

team_credits.name: Delightful Children From Down The Lane

description: Good morning, and welcome to the second day of your stay in Electric City. We are your providers, the Global Peace Agency. Time to take a dip in the Time Pool. What's the worst that can happen? You are a valued guest. You can leave any time you want. You have nothing to fear. You will tell us everything.
name: Part 2: Pawns

description: The future begins now! Join us as we present pop culture's first hero -- Buck Rogers! The first man out of time the first man to be taken from his present and thrown into the future the inspiration for countless heroes, and it all begins here! From the thrilling adventure presented in Dynamite's introductory issue #0 last month, the creative team of writer Scott Beatty, artist Carlos Rafael and 50/50 cover artists Alex Ross and John Cassaday (Cassaday serves as the regular cover artist for the series) present this all-new issue #1! In the tradition of modern stories for iconic legendary heroes, Buck Rogers is the next BIG hit series from Dynamite! Join us for an all-new presentation of this classic sci-fi hero as the future truly begins now! Hey, we could tell you more, but that would ruin the surprise of the comic adventure!
name: Future Shock, Part 1 - One Giant Leap

description: Galactus! He's devoured worlds since the dawn of the universe. Consuming the Korbinites' home was nothing special. But for Beta Ray Bill – oathbrother to Thor and the Korbinites' defender – it was a failure of his life's duty...and has given him a certain clarity. How can a hero suffer such a threat to his existence? Beta Ray Bill sets forth to hunt down Galactus, force him to his knees and make him pay – with a plan so audacious even the Planet Eater will feel fear...
name: Godhunter

description: What happens when Ben meets his match? Or rather, his mimic? Trouble, that's what! ?
name: Nemesis; Operation: T.R.A.D.E.; The Height Of Heat

description: Ben blasts off for space adventure! Plus, learn the secret scoop about Wildmutt!
name: Space Camp And Beyond; Charmed To Meet Me; Alien Data Files: Wildmutt; Operation: V.A.N.I.L.L.A.; Operation: C.H.O.C.O.L.A.T.E.; Operation: S.T.R.A.W.B.E.R.R.Y.

first_appearance_teams.name: Delightful Children From Down The Lane

team_credits.name: Delightful Children From Down The Lane

description: 'One Nation, Under Archie,' Part 1. Archie and his friends head for Washington, D.C. to take part in a living history festival where everyone dons costumes of their favorite historical figures! Does Archie have what it takes to portray a Revolutionary War hero? Will Betty and Veronica fight over who will wear the Medieval Princess gown? Can Jughead rustle up some grub as a wild west cowboy? What kind of scoundrel will Reggie dress as? It's a trip through history filled with laughter and learning, as only the Archie gang can deliver!
name: Archie Is History

description: Ben! It's high adventure on the open road! Plus, Samurai Jack and the Kids Next Door!
name: Greasy Lightning; Alien Data Files: Heatblast; Operation: O.V.E.R.F.L.O.W.; Alien Data Files: Fourarms; Peace, Love & Eggs

description: The concluding issue of John Byrne’s Angel WWI epic! Half a mile above the blood soaked battlefields of France, Angel must face an ancient and terrible evil, while the fate of an Empire hangs in the balance.
name: Monsters

description: Anna Mercury is back in this summer's biggest epic! Warren Ellis' fiery red-head returns to once again explode into mad science-fiction action with the stellar art of Facundo Percio, returning from the smash-hit original series! A city-state from the strange superdimensional space of The Constellation sends a probe to Earth. To decide whether or not to make contact, the London office of the Constellation Project must send an agent through the fabric of the universe itself to the city of Three Souls Town, apparently populated by an oppressive society made of kidnapped humans. But that's not how it starts. It starts with Anna Mercury, Earth's top transuniversal explorer, under ray-gun attack in a city beyond space itself!

The penultimate "Emerald Eclipse" chapter is upon us as the breakout on Oa leads to vast devastation and death across the planet. As the War of Light rages, do Kyle Rayner, Guy Gardner, Kilowog and the rest of the Corps have the willpower to quell the riot and overcome the napalm-spewing Red Lanterns and the fear-spreading Sinestro Corps?
name: Emerald Eclipse Part 5

description: In an alternate past, where the Revolution has become the State, liberty has been destroyed and the gods now walk the Earth. Now, a new power is rising. Forged in the fiery bowels of the planet, Atomika is the first man-made deity, both a god of technology and of the 21st century. Now he must hunt down and kill the ancient gods who have ruled the world of man since the dawn of time, a quest that will change the fate of humanity, and shake the world to its very core!

The hottest new series of 2005 continues as Arohnir, the Revolution made flesh, unleashes his newest creation: The State, a superpowered strike force tasked with putting down rebellions against the government, no matter how innocent they may seem. For all is not well in the Red Empire, and as the engines of industry bore deeper into her flesh, Mother Russia screams out to the one person that can hear her... Atomika.

Far beyond the civilized boulevards of Moscow lies the wilderness of Siberia, home to beasts, half-men, dark and forgotten things, and the Golog. This massive prison warehouses criminals, dissidents, freedom fighters and fools. These damned men are held tight in the icy grip of Morosko, the merciless Frost God who is nourished and strengthened by the ever-growing number of souls arriving in the Golog. But Atomika will tolerate no other deity in his kingdom! He comes for Morosko, and there on the barren tundra these two titans will inevitably clash in the ultimate crusade as, in the distance, the Golog's prisoners watch, not knowing whether to pray for salvation...or death.

Atomika's journey takes him deep into Russia's vast, towering forests, home to the ancient nature god Leshi. For decades, the Father of the Woods has watched his domain get eaten away by the forces of industry and he realizes that his time on this plane is over. Leshi does not want to fight Atomika, he wants to give him a gift: the wisdom to rule the kingdom of men.

Drawn to the southeastern reaches of the empire, Atomika hunts his most elusive prey to date, Baba Yaga, the wild witch who has haunted children's nightmares for centuries. But what he finds is not some old crone; instead the dark lady is beautiful and powerful, traits which excite in Atomika something he has never felt before: lust.

"God is Red" part 7 of 12. Arohnir has come for what is his, the child Chernobyl. But how can Atomika give up the only creature he has ever truly loved? Meanwhile, the hunted has become the hunter as the forge god Khar-Kov makes an attack on Moscow itself, hoping to root out Atomika.

After fifteen years apart, Atomika is reunited with his son, but Chernobyl has changed. Under Arohnir's tutelage, he's become conceited, arrogant, and powerful - perhaps more powerful than Atomika himself. But when Zemliu, the gateway to Hell, is opened, father and son must fight side-by-side against an infernal army-a battle which will bring them together, or tear them apart once and for all.

Maddie receives a gift that reveals to her the truth behind her parents' divorce, while Ricky and Sora go on an impromptu date and Suzume nurses her wounds. Meanwhile, Meppy brings Kuro to her house so he can test out her ninja team with a practice fight. He meets the enthusiastic (and oddly Australian) Sun Wukong, Meppy's sister Kit (recently transferred from out of town) and Lilly, a bee girl who seems nice, but a little...clingy. Very clingy. In fact, she tends to stick to other living beings almost permanently. She quickly gets stuck on Kuro (or vice-versa), and the only way he won’t spend his life that way is to sleep with her!
name: Voices From Afar

description: As Ricky and Tetsuo's teams rest up for the final round of their training contest, Meppy spins a yarn about a foxy lady that her audience fails to find relevant, so they all split up and split. Ricky and Sora continue to hit it off, Tetsuo and Suzume nearly hit one another, Maddie hits the trail while Arthur hits the trees, and Kuro and Nanashi...well, you'll just have to see.
name: Date Night!

description: The training for young ninjas' survival continues--let the games begin! Tetsuo still demands a showdown with Ricky to prove his skills, so both teams head for a secret ninja island where they will engage in a fierce competition...of tagging each other with a soccer ball and reciting haiku. But what are decidedly non-ninja Arthur and Maddie doing there? And why does Meppy get to be the referee?
name: Bakuretsu Ball!

description: Somebody goofed up 25 years ago, and we're going to make it right! The one Star Trek movie that never got a proper comic book adaptation is the best one! Kirk, Spock and crew will battle it out with Khan for the last time!
name: Official Comic Adaptation pt. 1

volume.name: Star Trek II: The Wrath of Khan

description: Ricky, Kuro and Suzume begin their specialized ninja training, learning to work together for survival, but it Ricky and Suzume, at least, don't seem to be getting along. Meanwhile, Ricky's rival Tetsuo is rapidly honing his skills and teamwork with his own two lovely new partners, Soraand Nanashi. When Tetsuo decides to pull a midnight raid on Ricky to prove his skills, will Ricky be able to handle the assault on his own, or will his team pull together in time?
name: Night of the Ninjas!

description: With the threat of the Shidoshi clan growing, Lendo and Anna start training new recruits. Ricky finally heals enough physically from his battle with Kyonshi to begin that training, but he still has to deal with the mental scars--along with his new teammates.
name: Enter the Ninjas

description: Nightwing and Flamebird, meet Nadira Va-Dim and Az-Rel, the Bonnie and Clyde of Krypton. They've got all of your powers, but absolutely none of your morals. Good luck!
name: The Sleepers, Part 4

description:
THE MASTERS OF DOOM Part Two

The Marquis of Death has returned to Earth after a genocidal sojourn of two decades! And his first target is his once-pupil,

Victor Von Doom!
name: The Masters Of Doom, Part 2

description: The original X-Men have left the building, and their replacements have arrived! How will Cyclops cope with the next generation of mutants, far more powerful and far less careful? Find out in this giant-sized special, featuring untold tales from the X-Men's pasts! The 8-year-old Storm enters the deadly Museum of Set! Banshee clashes with the hordes of Irish myth! Nightcrawler fights alongside his circus family! Colossus battles to save his friends in Siberia! And at long last, Wolverine reveals his slice-your-heart-and-hope-to-die true origin in 'The Man from S.N.I.K.T.'!
name: Giant-Sized Special

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

volume.name: Uncanny X-Men: First Class Giant-Size Special

description:
Quarterly British comic reprinting the best stories from the pages of 2000AD and its spin-off titles. This issue collects the harder to find clashes between Judge Dredd and Judge Death (to tie in with the recently released Dredd vs Death computer game).

Wraparound cover: Jock (Judge Dredd)

  • Judge Dredd - House of Death (reprint from Diceman issue 1 - a choose your own adventure style comic story, where the reader chooses the outcome) (John Wagner and Alan Grant - Bryant Talbot)
  • Judge Dredd - What if Judges did Ads? (2000AD prog 521) (John Wagner and Alan Grant - Brett Ewins/Ian Gibson/Robin Smith/Kevin O'Neill/Cam Kennedy)
  • Judge Dredd - Theatre of Death (2000AD progs 700-701) (John Wagner - Ron Smith) (shows the final fate of Chief Judge Silver at the hands of Judge Death)
  • Judge Death - The True Story (2000AD progs 901-902) (John Wagner - Ian Gibson)
  • Judge Dredd - Dead Reckoning (2000AD progs 1000-1006) (John Wagner - Greg Staples)
name: Dredd vs Death

description:
1. Rex, King of the Deep

2. Captain Easy (by Roy Crane)

3. John Carter of Mars

4. Alley Oop (by V.T. Hamlin)

5. Bosko (written by Hugh Harman)

6. What Would You Do?

7. Mr. District Attorney

8. The Wonderland of Oz

9. Bosko (written by Hugh Harman)

10. Sky Ranger (by Bob Gaylord)

11. Whitey Harrison

12. The O'Malley Kids (by Win Smith)

13. Bosko (written by Hugh Harman)

14. Speed Martin

An All-American creative team tackles the celebrated Doctor in this special standalone tale. John Ostrander (Star Wars: Legacy) writes and Kelly Yates (Doctor Who: The Forgotten) illustrates an adventure where the Doctor and his companion Donna arrive on a utopian planet where robots do all the manual labor. But things aren't quite what they seem...
name: One-Shot

description:
Starting this issue, we begin one-shot "Day in the Life" stories. And this issue stars Cyborg! In the grueling aftermath of the "Deathtrap" arc, Vic Stone must face the very teammates he feels he let down big-time. How he deals with it will shock you! Garfield Logan (Beast Boy) and Vic Stone (Cyborg) have a conversation that ends with Garfield telling Vic that he has become more seperated from his human half, and that perhaps he should get a girlfriend.

Vic decides to get some air and he goes to see his old girlfriend Sarah, who is still teaching kids with disabilities. She ends up telling him the same thing. After the conversation Vic is walking through his old neighborhood when he notices that people are looking at him in fear. It turns out that an old friend who had his cybernetic implants removed, is now the head of a church that preaches against technology.

After a battle with a guy in a Nano suit, Vic discovers that Garfield signed him up with a dating service that pairs Metas with regular people. Nervous about the date, it ends up going well when vic discovers she too has her own disabilities that makes her rely on technology.
name: Disconnected

description: BE HERE FOR THE BEGINNING! Comics icon and New York Times bestselling writer Chris Claremont returns to his legendary run with X-MEN: FOREVER! The shockwaves after the death of Magneto are still reverberating all over the world. Attempting to heal the rift between man and mutant kind, Professor Xavier volunteers his X-Men to go on a mission to capture Magneto’s sole remaining Acolyte, Fabien Cortez! But with Nick Fury—and the entire world—watching over their shoulders, the stakes have never been higher for Cyclops, Jean Grey, Wolverine, Nightcrawler, Gambit, Rogue, Kitty Pryde, Storm, Beast, and Professor X. With Tom Grummet bringing Claremont’s vision to the page, this landmark series is packed with enough surprises and twists to shake the X-Men mythos to its very core!
name: Love and Loss!

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: “DIRTY SEXY MONET” Monet St. Croix: Smoking hot. Steamy. Gorgeous. Did we mention she was smoking hot? And suddenly she's taking charge of protecting X-Factor’s client from a serial killer while displaying extreme romantic interest in one of the team. Business as usual? Or something darkly sinister going on? And if you were the one Monet was coming on to, would you care?
name: Dirty, Sexy Monet

description:
A new generation of X-Men, a new generation of trouble! Twenty years have passed since the original X-Men faced their ultimate threat. Now, their children and grandchildren are picking up where they left off as Becka Monroe, Pavel Rasputin, Olivier Raven and the other members of the fledgling GeNext discover that being a super hero is not all fun and games. They travel to India with Hank "The Beast" McCoy and discover an insidious plot… But who is behind these dangerous assassins terrorizing Mumbai? And why do they seem so familiar?

*SPOILERS*

The team arrives in India to a robot going on a rampage, sati attacks but is defeated the team descends and destroys the robots. A mysteries dark haired woman watches all and after the robots defeat she triggers their self destruction then leaves in secret.

The team helps the injured then they are taken to the Indian superhero headquarters where they get a bath change clothes and get some food. Rico is obsessively fiddling with the robot part desperate to find out why its so familiar. He decides to go for a walk and sati accompanies him much to the dismay of Bekka who reveals she wishes he was doing so with her. Bekka is with beats as she watches no-name and pavel along with Megan and oli.

The woman from earlier arrives home only to be met by Kalima who is their to teach her a lesson as she has decided to come and play in her backyard, the woman in green screams.

Sati asks why rico keeps his brilliance to himself when he explains his love for music unlike his father and granddad who prefer science. She introduces him to her uncle who plays the sitar he catches on quick and her uncle wishes to have him as a student. After this they continue their stroll with him realizing where he knows the design from.

He carries them to a residence and Megan is taken out quickly by mental bolt and kalima tells them to flee. They don’t listen and a battle erupts. after they battle some demons and rescue the prisoner she wakes up and kisses Rico she is introduced as Sophie von doom, only child of doom and heir to latveria.
name: Passage To India, Part 2: This Lady Kills At Dawn

description: It all ends and begins right here! Araña learns what the future of the Wasp/Spider-Clan battle holds, and what it means for her destiny as the Hunter! Sides are chosen, lives are lost and Araña will never be the same!
name: The Hunter Revealed

description: Facing the rogue Gotham City police officer who was "created" by The Joker – Commissioner Gordon and Batman receive desperate help from an unusual source: young Barbara Gordon!
name: ...Bad Cop

description: Strange things are happening, and Captain Marvel is pretty sure it has something to do with a certain crazy doctor! With the help of two sentient cockroaches, Dr. Sivana has recently escaped from Fawcett City Penitentiary and set out to take over the world. Using the one skill he has -- being a mad scientist -- Sivana creates a robotic mayhem on the city of Fawcett. But he needs more power, and it would appear that his archenemies Captain Marvel and Mary Marvel might be just what the doctor ordered.
name: Mr. Who? Mr. Atom!

volume.name: Billy Batson and the Magic of SHAZAM!

description: The new lord of Kobra has shown his true face of evil, and now the JSA stands ready to face Kobra. But the old tactics may not work against this new terrorist network. Conspiracy mastermind Eric Trautmann (CHECKMATE, FINAL CRISIS: RESIST) and artist Don Kramer (DETECTIVE COMICS, NIGHTWING) take you inside the mind of Jason Burr, the diabolically clever Kobra leader whose goal is nothing less than bringing the world into the age of Kali Yuga. Set throughout the major cities of the DC Universe and wrapped in the gorgeous covers of Gene Ha (TOP 10), this 6-issue miniseries sets the stakes higher than ever before for the Justice Society!
name: Engines Of Faith, Part One: Bad Religion

description:
When Booster Gold learns of Batman's death, he visits the Batcave, but runs into a new Dark Knight. Fists will fly and Batman will die…again! And in the debut of a new 10-page co-feature, Blue Beetle is back! While enjoying a peaceful lunch with his friends, Jaime Reyes and all of El Paso, Texas are attacked by a marauding 50-foot robot, and only Blue Beetle can stop this mechanized monster.

Booster Gold

Rip Hunter discovers that someone else is one Vanishing Point and tries to track them down. He learns that Batman is "dead' and that the intruder is the Black Beetle. He barely escapes and calls Booster to his Time Lab. Once Booster arrives, from saving a elevator full of people without getting credit, the two Time Master argue over Batman's death. Rip insists that Booster go to the batcave and steal back the pictures of him trying to save Barbara Gordon.

Once in the cave Booster is jumped by Batman, who is later revealed as Dick Grayson. The two of them fight over the file mark Booster and Booster is forced to explain what he tried to do those years ago. Booster is about to revelto Dick that he isn't the fool everyone thinks he is the Black Beetle intrupts. Booster and Dick are too much for the villian and he escapes. Booster thinks he won but realizes Dick is gone and there are two Robin costumes in the classes behind him.

Skeets informs him the Black Beetle has changed history, and Dick had died at some point earlier.

Blue Beetle

Jamie, Paco and Brenda are hanging out at El Diablo when Thinko attacks the city. Jamie jumps into action and three hours later he has destoried the robot. The three friends go to see Doctor Alan Von Neumann, the man whose father was responsable for the first time the Robot attacked the city. He explains that he's been locked up and had nothing to do with the attack. The three friends are late for school and have to leave.

Outside of school Jamie confides in Paco that the scrab has been more "bloodthristy". He about to tell Paco a secret when they are attacked by a fleet of Unimates.
name: Day of Death, Part I of IV; Armor-Plated, Part 1 of 3: Golden Child

description: Jay Garrick faces a Viking wielding Mjolnir.
